  m_Name: FomoSO 4
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FomoFirewallSO
  Question: Oil jumps after breaking news.
  Desc: Oil jumps after breaking news.
  cmt1: Oil is unstoppable!
  cmt2: This rally is just getting started!
  cmt3: Buy now!
  CorrectOption: 4
  CorrectWhatHappenDec: You researched the reason behind the oil price increase before
    acting. Understanding the geopolitical event helped you make a more informed
    decision instead of reacting emotionally.
  CorrectLesson: Always understand why a market is moving before investing. Research
    reduces emotional decisions and helps you manage risk more effectively.
  WrongWhatHappenDec: You rushed into the trade immediately after seeing the headlines.
    Later, the market stabilized as investors reassessed the news, leaving your decision
    exposed to unnecessary risk.
  WrongLesson: Breaking news often creates emotional pressure. Acting without understanding
    the cause of a price movement can lead to poor investment decisions.
